name: Navtara Veg Restaurant

reviews.review_text: The food was good. Coffee was great. Service given by staff Alomgir was very efficient.

I WOULD HAVE GIVEN  MINUS RATING IF AVAILABLE.

Pathetic service provider I have ever experienced . Cafe Bhosale was half shutter down so we went to this outlet of Navtara at around 10.25pm. My wife went to the loo. And we were seating to place the order but the waiter Ganesh was busy with the other customers. After some time Ganesh came to take the order, to start with we had ordered  paneer tikka masala and cheese stuffed garlic naan. But he said only plain naan is available as the bhatti is cold. Roti or chapati is available. Then we went to the cashier MR. NARESH WHO WAS VERY RUDE, MISLEADING AND OVERSMART on counter. Requested him to give managers contact number as we were disappointed with the service. The cashier said he doesn't have managers number. Then I saw the managers number on no smoking board, called him and explained him the entire scenario.

IT WAS NOT ABOUT THE FOOD BUT ABOUT THE COMMUNICATION, BEHAVIOUR, HOSPITALITY TOWARDS THE CUSTOMER.

NAVTARA HOTEL CHAINS THIS PORVORIM OUTLET IS THE WORST. WE HAD ALSO ENJOYED OUR MEAL IN THE OTHER OUTLETS WHICH WERE GOOD.

THIS OUTLET OF NAVTARA NEEDS TO BE IMPROVED IN THEIR SERVICE STAFF ESPECIALLY MR. NARESH WHO SEATS ON THE COUNTER.

Worst service ever.
They will never agree to their fault.
Don't go here.
Because of them we have wasted so much food.

description:
**Restaurant Review: Navtara Veg Restaurant, Chorao**

Nestled in the charming locale of Chorao, **Navtara Veg Restaurant** boasts an impressive **4.1-star rating**, backed by a robust **9,600 reviews** from patrons. Signature offerings include **South Indian food** (frequently highlighted 103 times), as well as popular dishes like **pav bhaji** (39 times) and **puri bhaji** (26 times). These dishes encapsulate the establishment's commitment to vegetarian cuisine, appealing to both local tastes and visitors looking for authentic Indian flavors.

### Ambiance & Design
Stepping into Navtara, guests are greeted by a vibrant and warm atmosphere. Images from customer experiences showcase an inviting interior adorned with traditional Indian motifs, blending modern comfort with a touch of cultural heritage. The lighting casts a soft glow, creating a cozy setting ideal for both family gatherings and solo dining. Reviewers note the restaurant's comfortable seating arrangements, which enhance the overall dining experience. However, feedback on the ambiance is somewhat overshadowed by service issues, which some patrons have called out, leading to a mixed sentiment regarding the environment.

### Menu & Culinary Experience
Navtara's menu is a testament to its dedication to vegetarian cuisine, with a diverse array of offerings that prominently feature the **South Indian specialties** it’s known for. Signature dishes such as **paneer tikka masala** and a variety of **naans** are focal points, highlighting the bold flavors and aromatic spices characteristic of Indian cooking. While one customer enjoyed their **coffee** highly and appreciated the quality of the food, others had contrasting experiences that dampened their culinary enjoyment, specifically citing the **unavailability** of certain menu items during their visit. Customer images reveal well-presented plates, showcasing vibrant colors and appetizing arrangements, typical of South Indian culinary craftsmanship.

### Customer Experience & Service
The service at Navtara has become a defining aspect of its reputation, and unfortunately, not all reviews are glowing. While some diners commend the efficiency of staff like *Alomgir*, others describe starkly negative experiences with service, highlighting a lack of communication and hospitality. One review pointedly criticized *Mr. Naresh*, the cashier, for being rude and unhelpful, emphasizing that the core issue lay not with the food but with service interactions. Guests also noted their frustration with long wait times and perceived disinterest from the staff, which contributed to a disappointing dining experience. The establishment may benefit from focusing on customer service training to address these concerns.

### Popularity & Reviews
Despite the mixed reviews, Navtara continues to be a popular dining choice, reflecting a dichotomy of experiences. Online sentiment varies greatly, with some diners enjoying delightful meals and amicable service, while others have expressed their dissatisfaction with service quality to the point of contemplating a **lower rating**. Critically, there has been a noted absence of high-level accolades or media buzz that might elevate its status among vegetarian restaurants in the area, which could be important as it competes against other venues. 

### Utilizing Visual Content 
The engaging photos shared by customers provide insightful glimpses into both the atmosphere and culinary presentation at Navtara. The images reveal a bustling restaurant scene and artfully plated dishes that tantalize the senses. While the décor appears to resonate with a traditional Indian theme, the inconsistencies in service and experience come through in the stark contrasts of the posted reviews. Some visuals depict patrons enjoying their meals happily, while others convey the tension surrounding service mishaps, encapsulating the restaurant's current standing.

In conclusion, **Navtara Veg Restaurant** stands at a critical juncture where its culinary strengths, particularly in South Indian cuisine, shine through captivating dishes and inviting space. However, the recurring service issues highlighted in numerous reviews suggest a pressing need for improvement that, if addressed, could elevate the restaurant to new heights in both customer satisfaction and dining reputation.
